itable\" style=\"background:white\"\n! Insignia !! Rank !! Component !! Date\n|-\n|align=\"center\" |No insignia || [[Cadet#United States|Cadet]] || [[United States Military Academy]] || June 14, 1913\n|-\n|align=\"center\" |No pin insignia at the time || [[Second lieutenant#United States|Second lieutenant]] || [[Regular Army (United States)|Regular Army]] || April 20, 1917\n|-\n|align=\"center\" |[[File:US-O2 insignia.svg|13px]] || [[First lieutenant#United States|First lieutenant]] || Regular Army || May 15, 1917\n|-\n|align=\"center\" |[[File:US-O3 insignia.svg|33px]] || [[Captain (United States O-3)|Captain]] || Temporary || August 5, 1917\n|-\n|align=\"center\" |[[File:US-O4 insignia.svg|40px]] || [[Major (United States)|Major]] || Temporary || September 9, 1918\n|-\n|align=\"center\" |[[File:US-O3 insignia.svg|33px]] || [[Captain (United States O-3)|Captain]] || Regular Army || June 25, 1919  (Discharged as temporary major and resumed permanent rank of captain on March 10, 1920.)\n|-\n|align=\"center\" |[[File:US-O4 insignia.svg|40px]] || [[Major (United States)|Major]] || Regular Army || October 1, 1932\n|-\n|align=\"center\" |[[File:US-O5 insignia.svg|40px]] || [[Lieutenant colonel (United States)|Lieutenant colonel]] || Regular Army || June 25, 1940\n|-\n|align=\"center\" |[[File:US-O6 insignia.svg|60px]] || [[Colonel (United States)|Colonel]] || [[Army of the United States]] || January 13, 1941\n|-\n|align=\"center\" |[[File:US-O7 insignia.svg|33px]] || [[Brigadier general (United States)|Brigadier general]] || Army of the United States || February 14, 1942\n|-\n|align=\"center\" |[[File:US-O8 insignia.svg|66px]]  || [[Major general (United States)|Major general]] || Army of the United States || May 26, 1942\n|-\n|align=\"center\" |[[File:US-O9 insignia.svg|99px]] || [[Lieutenant general (United States)|Lieutenant general]] || Army of the United States || April 16, 1945\n|-\n|align=\"center\" |[[File:US-O7 insignia.svg|33px]] || [[Brigadier general (United States)|Brigadier general]] || Regular Army || June 19, 1945\n|-\n|align=\"center\" |[[File:US-O8 insignia.svg|66px]] || [[Major general (United States)|Major general]] || Regular Army || January 24, 1948\n|-\n|align=\"center\" |[[File:US-O10 insignia.svg|132px]] || [[General (United States)|General]] || Army of the United States || January 24, 1948\n|-\n|align=\"center\" |[[File:US-O10 insignia.svg|132px]] || [[General (United States)|General]] || Regular Army, Retired || March 31, 1956\n|-\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==References==\n*Joseph Lawton Collins (1969). ''War in peacetime: the history and lessons of Korea''.\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|J. Lawton Collins}}\n*[http://www.history.army.mil/books/cg&csa/Collins-JL.htm Joseph Lawton Collins biography] in ''Commanding Generals and Chiefs of Staff'' a publication of the [[United States Army Center of Military History]]\n*[http://cdm16635.contentdm.oclc.org/cdm/search/collection/p16635coll16/searchterm/collins%2C%20lawton/order/nosort J. Lawton Collins Collection Finding Aids] US Army Heritage and Education Center, Carlisle, Pennsylvania\n*[http://www.arlingtoncemetery.net/josephla.htm Arlington National Cemetery Biography]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20060614004301/http://www-cgsc.army.mil/carl/resources/csi/wade3/wade3.asp Conversations with General J. Lawton Collins], Combat Studies Institute report\n*[http://eisenhower.archives.gov/Research/Finding_Aids/C.html Papers of J. Lawton Collins, Dwight D. Eisenhower Presidential Library]\n*[http://eisenhower.archives.gov/Research/Finding_Aids/W.html Papers of John J. Walsh (Aide-de-Camp to J. Lawton Collins), Dwight D. Eisenhower Presidential Library]\n*{{Find a Grave|4633}}\n* {{Internet Archive film clip|id=gov.archives.arc.39048|description=AIR ASSAULT TACTICS ETC. (1945)}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-mil}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Maxwell Murray]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[25th Infantry Division (United States)|Commanding General 25th Infantry Division]]|years=